00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.920
In a word which is very often used in the Welsh is top,

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:12.400
which is what I am for being up here.

00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:14.920
That means being silly.

00:00:14.920 --> 00:00:19.720
Oh, I've taken a real fancy to her, they go, and...

00:00:19.720 --> 00:00:22.200
She was out there like a winky.

00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:23.600
These are terms which they use,

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:27.400
and of course you have to understand these connotations.

00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:29.560
For example, it's the last thing I am now,

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:31.560
but when somebody is excited, they say,

00:00:31.560 --> 00:00:33.560
Oh, he's over the moon, he is.

00:00:33.560 --> 00:00:35.560
Ha!

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:38.960
Shukum rynchid.

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:42.160
A real blemmer.

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:44.560
Waretig, waretig.

00:00:44.560 --> 00:00:46.160
We should be fair play in Welsh.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:49.160
These are words which cover the language here,

00:00:49.160 --> 00:00:52.360
catryl and gwa'dab and all the rest of it.

00:00:52.360 --> 00:00:55.760
The one with the kind of term which would...

00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:59.360
One of the ones which I really take a fancy to is that

00:00:59.360 --> 00:01:01.160
the kind of thing when somebody asks you,

00:01:01.160 --> 00:01:03.160
Oh, how's your sister?

00:01:03.160 --> 00:01:04.960
Oh, very poor.

00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:06.960
She's under the doctor, she is.

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:08.960
Ha!

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:18.360
It strikes me as a sure case of malpractice, eh?

00:01:18.360 --> 00:01:20.360
Ha!

